   Joseph Eid, The music over the ruins of Aleppo from AFP Correspondent.

   I came across this extraordinary photograph a few weeks ago and
   immediately thought of the title of one of Albert Ayler’s albums, an
   avant-garde jazz saxophonist, singer and composer: Music is the Healing
   Power of the Universe. Upon further reading, I learned more about
   Mohammed Anis and his determination to live, and to begin anew in the
   ruins that are today his hometown of Aleppo. Read about his story here.

