     * 140 notes

     * Thomas Merton
     * humility
     * Wisdom Traditions

     * Wednesday 5th September 2018

   “In humility is the greatest freedom. As long as you have to defend the
   imaginary self that you think is important, you lose your peace of
   heart. As soon as you compare that shadow with the shadows of other
   people, you lose all joy, because you have...

   “In humility is the greatest freedom. As long as you have to defend the
   imaginary self that you think is important, you lose your peace of
   heart. As soon as you compare that shadow with the shadows of other
   people, you lose all joy, because you have begun to trade in
   unrealities and there is no joy in things that do not exist.”

   —Thomas Merton, with thanks to louie, louie. Photo found at OSV
   Newsweekly.

     * Tags
     * Thomas Merton
     * humility
     * Wisdom Traditions

